text: The capacity of the essential oils obtained from the aerial parts or from the fruits of Foeniculum vulgare for scavenging hydroxyl radicals was always less than 50 % , at the concentrations assayed ( 100 - 2 , 000 mg / mL ) [ 57 ] . Mannitol , the reference used in this assay , showed a similar scavenging percentage at ≈ 2 , 000 mg / mL . Only higher concentrations presented percentages > 50 % .
